Package at.fhj.iit

Interface IQueue<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
GenericQueue, StringQueue
public interface IQueue<T>

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    T element()
    It works similar to peek() but with a small difference (returns but does not delete the element).
    boolean offer​(T obj)
    Adds the element obj to the queue.
    T peek()
    Returns the head element but it does not delete it.
    T poll()
    Returns the head (first) element and also deletes it.
    T remove()
    It also returns and deletes the head element like poll(), but with a small difference.

  • Method Details

    • offer

      boolean offer​(T obj)
      Adds the element obj to the queue. If the addition is successful, the method returns true else false.
      Parameters:
      obj - the element which should get added to the queue
      Returns:
      true if adding an element to the queue worked; false if not

    • poll

      T poll()
      Returns the head (first) element and also deletes it. That is, we cannot get it again. If no element exists (when queue is empty), the method returns null.
      Returns:
      the first element in the queue

    • remove

      T remove()
      It also returns and deletes the head element like poll(), but with a small difference. This method throws NoSuchElementException if the queue is empty.
      Returns:
      the first element in the queue

    • peek

      T peek()
      Returns the head element but it does not delete it. That is, we can get it again. Returns null when the queue is empty.
      Returns:
      the first element in the queue

    • element

      T element()
      It works similar to peek() but with a small difference (returns but does not delete the element). It throws NoSuchElementException when the queue is empty.
      Returns:
      the first element in the queue
